        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10933",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "If the last section in the draft version of the ZF Coding Standard is followed, then a simple require_once for Zend_Config_Ini would suffice, with the current version of loadClass().  See http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/x\/PQ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-10-02T01:09:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-10-02T01:09:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10934",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Lets keep alternative solutions all grouped under the same issue -i.e. addressing loadClass().",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-10-02T01:13:54.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-10-02T01:13:54.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10936",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ixti",
                        "name": "ixti",
                        "displayName": "Aleksey V. Zapparov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ok. I've read http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/x\/PQ\nBut don't clearly understood how this connects with my topic.\nAs I've read in ZF-329 loadClass will not be deprecated, so my\nversion of \"multi-call\" imho is still actual :)\nAnyway, i'll join ZF-329 discussion.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ixti",
                        "name": "ixti",
                        "displayName": "Aleksey V. Zapparov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-10-02T01:56:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-10-02T01:56:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10938",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "If Zend_Config_Array conforms to the draft, proposed Coding Standards, then:\n\n\"If a component uses another component, then the using component is responsible for loading the other component. If the use is conditional, then the loading should also be conditional.\"\n\nThus, if you want to use Zend_Config_Array, simply use:\n{{require 'Zend\/Config\/Array.php';}}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-10-02T02:31:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-10-02T02:31:31.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10939",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ixti",
                        "name": "ixti",
                        "displayName": "Aleksey V. Zapparov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Maybe you are right, but for me\n{code}\nZend::LoadClass{'Zend_Config,Zend_Config_Array');\n{code}\n\nseems much naturally then:\n{code}\nZend::loadClass('Zend_Config');\nrequire_once 'Zend\/Config\/Array.php';\n{code}\n\nIn this case even\n{code}\nrequire_once 'Zend.php';\nrequire_once 'Zend\/Config.php';\nrequire_once 'Zend\/Config\/Array.php';\n{code}\n\nwill be more naturally ,then mixing Zend::loadClass() and require_once. And reason I explained in ZF-329",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ixti",
                        "name": "ixti",
                        "displayName": "Aleksey V. Zapparov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-10-02T03:01:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-10-02T03:01:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10940",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{{Zend\/Config\/Array.php}} already {{require_once}}'s {{Zend\/Config.php}}, so you don't need {{Zend::loadClass('Zend_Config');}}.\n\nThe entire ZF library does not use loadInterface(), and loadClass() is only used twice in two factory methods.\n\nI think the ZF code provides a good example of when and how to use {{require_once}} and loadClass().",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-10-02T11:01:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-10-02T11:01:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10945",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ixti",
                        "name": "ixti",
                        "displayName": "Aleksey V. Zapparov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{quote}Zend\/Config\/Array.php already require_once's Zend\/Config.php, so you don't need Zend::loadClass('Zend_Config');.{quote}\n\nNeither _Zend_Config_Array doesn't require_once's in Zend_Config_\nnor _Zend_Config doesn't require_once's Zend_Config_Array_ (at least in 0.1.5 version)\nSo here an example: http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.config.html\n\nAnd that was what I'm talking about. Zend::loadClass has not to be used inside of ZF library,\nbut it has to be available for developers to use it outside... IMHO :)\n\nAnyway, I guess, accroding to rules, my opinion means nothing :)\nI just wanted to improve loadClass, but if core team thinks that it has to be deprecated,\nthen let it be.\n\nPS Anyway I can copy-paste it from version to version for my purposes...",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ixti",
                        "name": "ixti",
                        "displayName": "Aleksey V. Zapparov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-10-03T03:37:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-10-03T03:37:06.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10947",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Development discussions in JIRA issues and the mail lists normally refer only to the SVN head version of ZF, not past releases.\n\n$ svn update\n\n$ grep -n require Config\/Array.php\n26:require_once 'Zend\/Config.php';\n\n$ grep -n require Config\/Ini.php\n26:require_once 'Zend\/Config.php';\n\nThe example in the manual is wrong.  The first require of Config.php is not needed.\n\nAlso loadClass() is used in the ZF, in a couple of factory methods, as I mentioned earlier.\n\n{quote}I just wanted to improve {{loadClass()}}, but if core team thinks that it has to be deprecated,\nthen let it be.{quote}\n\nI'm confused.  Nobody has said anything about deprecating loadClass().  In fact, I have been presenting reasons why it must be kept.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-10-03T10:50:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-10-03T10:50:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10951",
